Reasons as to why this was a bad plot

For starters, there is no clean cut story the data entails. The data was never filtered out so the data itself is not very tidy. But getting to the more aesthetic appeal of this plot, itâs not a positive eye catcher but it will turn heads. On a positive note there is a title, subtitle and axes. However, they are at the worst text size and colors. I apologize in advance to anyone who is red/green colorblind, this is severely difficult to read and interpret. The title and subtitles give no actual meaningful summary, suggestion or overview about what this plot is even about. The background is an unpleasant neon green that is not extremely appealing or pleasing to the eye as well as similar in color to the title and subtitles. There are images in inappropriate places and do not correlate to the breast cancer data set I was using.The visualizations of the y axis scale in particular is too big in my opinion which can make it misleading when attempting to interpret in which breast is cancer most commonly found in individuals from 20-70 year olds.It has poor grid lines making it even more unappealing. It has a legend that does not correlate to the actual data that was used. The bar plot colors were based off of the beyonce palette, so it was a step up from just keeping it to the original base R colors. However, the size of the plot is tiny meaning it is difficult to read and not clear about what this plot is depicting. It poorly communicates data in an irresponsible manner. All in all, I do not think this plot looks awesome in the slightest way. This would definitely not follow reproducible protocol.

Reasons as to why this was a good plot

To begin, the colors follow a theme of shades of pretty pastels within this density plot. The data is more clear as there are not too many variables, so I thought a legend would not be necessary. I filtered out the 3 highest ranges of tumor sizes and compared them to its potential degree of malignancy. The data is not difficult to follow as none of the colors are the same and the x axes are properly labeled at a reasonable size. It is also a bit more inclusive when it comes to people with colorblind conditions. The title and subtitle provide meaningful information that will help the individual understand what this plot is showing in regards to breast cancer and risk of a malignant tumor based on its size. I think itâs pretty awesome as itâs simple and straightforward.
